{"article_id":"9yjedE4ChTT3QEX6","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Washington ( CNN ) -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Support for the country 's new health care law has dropped to a record low ,","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"according to a new national poll .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"And a CNN/ORC International survey","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"released Monday","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"also indicates","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"that most Americans predict","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"that the Affordable Care Act will actually result in higher prices for their own medical care .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"Only 35 % of those","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"questioned in the poll say","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"they support the health care law , a 5-point drop in less than a month .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"Sixty-two percent say","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"they oppose the law , up four points from November .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"Nearly all of the newfound opposition is coming from women .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"`` Opposition to Obamacare rose six points among women , from 54 % in November to 60 % now ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"while opinion of the new law remained virtually unchanged among men , ''","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"CNN Polling Director Keating Holland said .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"`` That 's bad news for an administration","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"that is reaching out to moms across the country in an effort","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"to make Obamacare a success . ''","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"According to the survey ,","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"43 % say","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"they oppose the health care law","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"because it is too liberal ,","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"with 15 % saying","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"they give the measure a thumbs down","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"because it is not liberal enough .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"That means half the public either favors Obamacare ,","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"or opposes it","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"because it 's not liberal enough , down four points from last month .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"Sixty-three percent say","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"they believe","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"the new law will increase the amount of money","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"they personally pay for medical care ,","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"which may not be a good sign for a law","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"known as the `` Affordable Care Act . ''","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"The survey also indicates","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"that 42 % say","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"they will be personally worse off under Obamacare ,","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"with 16 % saying","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"the law will help them ,","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"and four in 10 saying","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"it will have no effect on them .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"Just over six in 10 say","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"they believe","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"they will be able to receive care from the same doctors","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"that they now use ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"with 35 % saying","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"they will not be able to see the same doctors .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"The Affordable Care Act ,","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"which is the signature domestic achievement for President Barack Obama ,","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"was passed along party lines in 2010 ,","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"when Democrats controlled both houses of Congress .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Since that passage , Republicans have fought to either repeal , defund , or severely restrict the law .","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"A push by congressional conservatives","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"to defund the law","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"was the catalyst for October 's 16-day long partial federal government shutdown , the first in nearly two decades .","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"The roll out of the law was extremely flawed , from the rocky startup of HealthCare.gov in October to the controversy","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"over millions of Americans","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"being told","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"they would lose their current insurance plans","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"because they did n't meet standards","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"mandated by the new health care law .","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"Despite all the problems , the President said","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"things are starting to improve ,","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"adding","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"that more than 500,000 Americans enrolled in the Affordable Care Act through HealthCare.gov during the first three weeks of December .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"`` So all told , millions of Americans ,","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"despite problems with the website ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"are now poised to be covered by quality affordable health care , ''","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"he said at a news conference .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"The poll was conducted for CNN by ORC International December 16-19 ,","depth":4},{"id":72,"text":"with 1,035 adults nationwide questioned by telephone .","depth":4},{"id":73,"text":"The survey 's overall sampling error is plus or minus three percentage points .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":147,"left":0,"right":146,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":146,"left":143,"right":145,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":121,"right":142,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":92,"right":120,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":92,"left":80,"right":91,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":80,"left":75,"right":79,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":75,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":79,"left":77,"right":78,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"paren